Seven ODM MPs yesterday issued a seven-day ultimatum to Deputy President William Ruto&rsquo;s aide Farouk Kibet, Transport CS James Macharia and PS Nicholas Muraguri to vacate office, failing which they will lead nationwide mass protests against them.Addressing a press conference at Parliament Building, Andrew Toboso (Butere), John Mbadi (Suba), Opiyo Wandayi (Ugunja), Oburu Oginga (Nominated), Peter Kaluma (Homa Bay Town), Timothy Bosire (Kitutu Masaba) and TJ Kajwang&rsquo; (Ruaraka) demanded President Uhuru Kenyatta and Ruto apologise to Kenyans for &ldquo;misleading them on the National Youth Service scandal&rdquo;.&ldquo;When the NYS scandal came to the public domain, none other than Uhuru and Ruto came to the defence of Waiguru when the opposition raised questions,&rdquo; they said in a statement read by Toboso.They said the scandal and Mafya House implicate Uhuru and Ruto&rsquo;s close associates and both should tell the nation what they know. &ldquo;We demand accountability,&rdquo; the MPs said.